oc:kn_10eb11e9 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any competitor alternative page" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Start every competitor comparison page with a TL;DR summary that names both competitor strengths and weaknesses, your differentiators, and clear 'choose X if' guidance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most visitors scan before reading; a TL;DR captures attention and communicates positioning immediately." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1158f992 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating competitor alternative pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include a migration section covering what transfers, what needs reconfiguration, migration support offered, and customer quotes about switching." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prospects evaluating alternatives need to assess switching costs; addressing migration directly reduces friction and anxiety." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_2f59880b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring comparison tables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Organize features into meaningful categories: core functionality, collaboration, integrations, security & compliance, support & service. Include star ratings where useful." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Categorized groupings help prospects find relevant comparisons quickly; ratings provide at-a-glance quality signals." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_349e235d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating the audience targeting section" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Who Should Choose [Competitor]
[Competitor] is the right choice if: [bulleted criteria]
**Ideal [Competitor] customer**: [Persona]

## Who Should Choose [Your Product]
[Your product] is built for teams who: [bulleted criteria]
**Ideal [Your product] customer**: [Persona]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Competitor",
        "Persona",
        "Your Product",
        "criteria" .

oc:kn_75ca9415 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating feature comparison sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use pure binary checkmark tables (✓/✗) for feature comparisons. Always describe the degree and quality of support." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Binary comparisons are misleading — two products may both 'support' a feature but with vastly different depth or quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7628612b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any feature comparison table" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Go beyond simple checkmarks in comparison tables. Use descriptive capability text like 'Full support with [detail]' vs 'Basic support, [limitation]' instead of ✓/✗ marks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Descriptive comparisons are more persuasive and honest than binary checkmarks, helping prospects make informed decisions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_923c5e79 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing feature, pricing, or support comparisons" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For each major comparison dimension, write a narrative paragraph — not just a table. Describe the competitor's approach honestly including strengths and limitations, then contrast with your approach." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Paragraph comparisons provide nuance and context that tables alone cannot convey, building trust through balanced coverage." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cc85c5db a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building a complete competitor comparison page" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Start with TL;DR summary (strengths, weaknesses, choose-if guidance). 2. Write paragraph comparisons for each major dimension. 3. Build descriptive feature comparison table organized by category. 4. Add pricing table with total cost consideration and value comparison. 5. Include service & support comparison. 6. Add 'Who It's For' section for both products. 7. Create migration section. 8. Add social proof from switchers." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_d343881f a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing feature comparison subsections" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## [Feature Category]
**[Competitor]**: [2-3 sentence description]
- Strengths: [specific]
- Limitations: [specific]

**[Your product]**: [2-3 sentence description]
- Strengths: [specific]
- Limitations: [specific]

**Bottom line**: Choose [Competitor] if [scenario]. Choose [You] if [scenario].""" .

oc:kn_dc005393 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating pricing comparison sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Pricing

| | [Competitor] | [Your Product] |
|---|---|---|
| Free tier | [Details] | [Details] |
| Starting price | $X/user/mo | $X/user/mo |
| Business tier | $X/user/mo | $X/user/mo |
| Enterprise | Custom | Custom |""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Competitor",
        "Details",
        "X",
        "Your Product" .

oc:kn_fe8b0c64 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the opening TL;DR section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "**TL;DR**: [Competitor] excels at [strength] but struggles with [weakness]. [Your product] is built for [your focus], offering [key differentiator]. Choose [Competitor] if [their ideal use case]. Choose [You] if [your ideal use case]." ;
    oc:templateVariables "Competitor",
        "key differentiator",
        "strength",
        "their ideal use case",
        "weakness",
        "your focus",
        "your ideal use case" .

